---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Section from '@/components/landing/Section.astro';
import CTA from '@/components/landing/CTA.astro';
import TopicCard from '@/components/landing/TopicCard.astro';
import StatCard from '@/components/landing/StatCard.astro';
import PricingCalculator from '@/components/landing/PricingCalculator';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
import { getAsset } from '@/utils/image';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';

const profileImage = await getAsset('profile.jpg');
const email = 'nick@nisi.org';
const subject = 'AI-Native Training Inquiry';
const bookingUrl = 'https://calendly.com/nicknisi/ai-engineer';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="The AI-Native Engineer | Nick Nisi"
	description="Help your engineering team thrive with AI. Live, tailored training that turns strong engineers into AI-native builders."
	fullWidth
>
	{/* Section 1: Hero */}
	<Section variant="hero" class="text-center">
		{/* Decorative gradient backdrop */}
		<div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden" aria-hidden="true">
			<div class="absolute -top-1/2 left-1/2 h-[800px] w-[800px] -translate-x-1/2 rounded-full bg-purple-500/15 blur-3xl" />
			<div class="absolute -bottom-1/2 right-0 h-[600px] w-[600px] rounded-full bg-teal-500/10 blur-3xl" />
		</div>
		<div class="relative z-10">
			<h1 class="font-serif text-6xl leading-tight font-bold tracking-tight md:text-8xl">
				The AI-Native Engineer
			</h1>
			<p class="gradient-text mx-auto mt-6 max-w-2xl text-xl font-semibold md:text-2xl">
				You're not being replaced. You're being promoted.
			</p>
			<p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-purple-200">
				The job is shifting from writing every line of code to directing the build.
				Your engineering judgment is more valuable than ever — if you know how to wield it.
			</p>
			<div class="mt-10 flex flex-col items-center gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:justify-center">
				<CTA href={bookingUrl} label="Book a Call" />
				<CTA email={email} subject={subject} label="Or Email Me" variant="secondary" />
			</div>
		</div>
	</Section>

	{/* Section 2: The Problem */}
	<Section variant="default" narrow>
		<h2 class="text-center font-serif text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl">
			The Ground Is Shifting Under Every Engineering Team
		</h2>
		<div class="mt-8 space-y-4 text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
			<p>
				Leadership is mandating AI adoption. Engineers are caught between the hype and the fear.
				Competitors are shipping faster. And the gap between "we use Copilot" and actually being
				AI-native is wider than anyone wants to admit.
			</p>
			<p>
				The anxiety is real. But the problem isn't AI — it's that nobody's showing teams
				how to actually work with it. Not toy demos. Not prompt engineering tips.
				Real workflows that change how you build software.
			</p>
		</div>
	</Section>

	{/* Section 3: The Reframe */}
	<Section variant="accent" class="border-l-4 border-purple-500">
		<h2 class="text-center font-serif text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl">
			AI Doesn't Replace Engineers. It Demands Better Ones.
		</h2>
		<div class="mx-auto mt-8 max-w-3xl space-y-4 text-xl text-gray-700 md:text-2xl dark:text-gray-300">
			<p>
				Code is becoming an artifact, not the craft itself. The craft is knowing <em>what</em> to build,
				<em>why</em> to build it, and <em>how</em> to verify it's right. That's <strong class="gradient-text">engineering judgment</strong> — and
				AI can't do it for you.
			</p>
			<p>
				Your years of experience aren't obsolete. <strong class="gradient-text">They're your superpower.</strong> The engineers who thrive
				aren't the ones who type the fastest — they're the ones who think the clearest.
			</p>
			<p>
				This is the most fun it's ever been to build software. Let's make sure your team is in on it.
			</p>
		</div>
	</Section>

	{/* Section 4: Social Proof / Stats */}
	<Section variant="muted" class="scroll-reveal">
		<div class="fade-up-grid grid grid-cols-2 gap-8 md:grid-cols-4">
			<StatCard value="3x" label="GitHub contributions in one year" />
			<StatCard value="0" label="Lines of code written by hand in 6 months" />
			<StatCard value="50+" label="Conference talks delivered" />
			<StatCard value="Staff" label="Engineer building AI-native at scale" />
		</div>
		<p class="mx-auto mt-8 max-w-2xl text-center text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
			Built the WorkOS CLI AI Installer — a production agent that configures, validates, and ships
			SDK integrations autonomously. Spent a full year as a solo DX engineer, maintaining 20+ repos
			on GitHub with AI-native workflows. This isn't theory. It's how I work every day.
		</p>
	</Section>

	{/* Section 5: Curriculum — Core Modules */}
	<Section variant="default" class="scroll-reveal">
		<h2 class="text-center font-serif text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl">
			What Your Team Will Learn
		</h2>
		<p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-2xl text-center text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
			A baseline curriculum tailored to your team's stack, experience, and goals.
		</p>
		<div class="fade-up-grid mx-auto mt-12 max-w-4xl space-y-12">
			{/* Step 1 — left */}
			<div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-6 md:flex-row">
				<div class="flex shrink-0 items-center gap-4">
					<div class="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-purple-700 text-lg font-bold text-white">1</div>
					<Icon name="mdi:swap-horizontal" class="size-10 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200" />
				</div>
				<div>
					<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">The Shift</h3>
					<p class="mt-1 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Why AI changes the job but not the craft. Mental models for working with agents. Your experience is your superpower.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			{/* Step 2 */}
			<div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-6 md:flex-row">
				<div class="flex shrink-0 items-center gap-4">
					<div class="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-purple-700 text-lg font-bold text-white">2</div>
					<Icon name="mdi:text-box-search-outline" class="size-10 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200" />
				</div>
				<div>
					<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Context is Everything</h3>
					<p class="mt-1 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">How to give AI the right context. Prompt engineering for code, tool selection, structuring projects for AI comprehension.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			{/* Step 3 — left */}
			<div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-6 md:flex-row">
				<div class="flex shrink-0 items-center gap-4">
					<div class="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-purple-700 text-lg font-bold text-white">3</div>
					<Icon name="mdi:drawing" class="size-10 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200" />
				</div>
				<div>
					<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Architecture-First Thinking</h3>
					<p class="mt-1 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">When code is cheap, design matters more. Systems thinking, tradeoff analysis, making the decisions agents can't.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			{/* Step 4 */}
			<div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-6 md:flex-row">
				<div class="flex shrink-0 items-center gap-4">
					<div class="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-purple-700 text-lg font-bold text-white">4</div>
					<Icon name="mdi:check-decagram-outline" class="size-10 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200" />
				</div>
				<div>
					<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Review, Verify, Ship</h3>
					<p class="mt-1 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">You're an editor, not a writer. Evaluating AI output, catching subtle bugs, testing what you didn't write.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			{/* Step 5 — left */}
			<div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-6 md:flex-row">
				<div class="flex shrink-0 items-center gap-4">
					<div class="flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-purple-700 text-lg font-bold text-white">5</div>
					<Icon name="mdi:source-branch" class="size-10 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200" />
				</div>
				<div>
					<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Working in Parallel</h3>
					<p class="mt-1 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Managing multiple workstreams simultaneously. Practical workflows for 3x-ing your output with agents.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</Section>

	{/* Section 6: Customizable Add-ons */}
	<Section variant="muted">
		<h2 class="text-center font-serif text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl">
			Customize the Depth
		</h2>
		<p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-2xl text-center text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
			Every engagement starts with the core curriculum. Add focus areas based on your team's needs.
		</p>
		<div class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-2xl space-y-4">
			<div class="flex items-start gap-3">
				<Icon name="mdi:account-group-outline" class="mt-1 size-6 shrink-0 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200" />
				<div>
					<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Team Adoption Strategies</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">For engineering managers — rolling out AI workflows across the org without the chaos.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="flex items-start gap-3">
				<Icon name="mdi:magnify" class="mt-1 size-6 shrink-0 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200" />
				<div>
					<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Tool Selection & Evaluation</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Choosing the right AI tools for your stack and evaluating them rigorously.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="flex items-start gap-3">
				<Icon name="mdi:shield-check-outline" class="mt-1 size-6 shrink-0 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200" />
				<div>
					<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Internal Conventions & Guardrails</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Setting team standards for AI usage — style guides, review policies, and quality gates.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</Section>

	{/* Section 7: How It Works */}
	<Section variant="default">
		<h2 class="text-center font-serif text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl">
			Built for How Teams Actually Learn
		</h2>
		<div class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-1 gap-10 md:grid-cols-3">
			<div class="text-center">
				<Icon name="mdi:account-group-outline" class="mx-auto mb-4 size-12 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200" />
				<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Live & Interactive</h3>
				<p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
					Not pre-recorded. Real-time instruction, Q&A, and pair programming.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="text-center">
				<Icon name="mdi:cog-outline" class="mx-auto mb-4 size-12 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200" />
				<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Tailored to Your Stack</h3>
				<p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
					Curriculum adapted to your team's languages, frameworks, and real projects.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="text-center">
				<Icon name="mdi:layers-outline" class="mx-auto mb-4 size-12 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200" />
				<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Baseline + Customize</h3>
				<p class="mt-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
					Start with the core. Go deeper where your team needs it most.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</Section>

	{/* Section 8: Instructor */}
	<Section variant="muted" class="scroll-reveal">
		<h2 class="text-center font-serif text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl">
			Meet Your Instructor
		</h2>
		<div class="mt-12 flex flex-col items-center gap-8 md:flex-row md:items-start">
			<Image
				src={profileImage}
				alt="Nick Nisi"
				width={256}
				height={256}
				quality="max"
				class="h-48 w-48 shrink-0 rounded-full object-cover shadow-lg"
			/>
			<div>
				<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					Nick Nisi is a Staff Engineer who hasn't written a line of code by hand in six months — and his
					output has never been higher. He built the WorkOS CLI AI Installer, a production agent that
					configures and ships SDK integrations autonomously. He's delivered 50+ conference talks, been a
					host on <a href="https://jsparty.fm" class="font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200">JS Party</a>,
					and contributed to open source across the TypeScript ecosystem.
				</p>
				<div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-6 text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
					<span>50+ Conference Talks</span>
					<span>Staff Engineer</span>
					<span>JS Party Alum</span>
					<span>Open Source</span>
				</div>
				<p class="mt-4">
					<a href="/about" class="font-bold text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-200">Full bio &rarr;</a>
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</Section>

	{/* Section 9: Who It's For */}
	<Section variant="default">
		<h2 class="text-center font-serif text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl">
			Is This Right for Your Team?
		</h2>
		<div class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-1 gap-10 md:grid-cols-2">
			<div>
				<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-green-700 dark:text-green-400">Great Fit</h3>
				<ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					<li>Engineers feeling the AI shift and wanting to get ahead of it</li>
					<li>Teams with AI adoption mandates from leadership</li>
					<li>Companies that see competitors pulling ahead with AI</li>
					<li>Engineers who want to build more and type less</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h3 class="p-0 font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-red-600 dark:text-red-400">Not a Fit</h3>
				<ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
					<li>Looking for a course on building AI/ML models</li>
					<li>Non-technical roles</li>
					<li>Teams already fully AI-native</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</Section>

	{/* Section 10: Pricing Calculator */}
	<Section variant="dark">
		<PricingCalculator client:only="react" bookingUrl={bookingUrl} email={email} />
	</Section>

	{/* Section 11: FAQ */}
	<Section variant="muted" narrow>
		<h2 class="text-center font-serif text-3xl font-bold md:text-4xl">
			Common Questions
		</h2>
		<div class="mt-12 space-y-4">
			<details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-5 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-purple-300 dark:border-dark-border dark:bg-dark-surface dark:hover:border-purple-700">
				<summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
					<span>What makes this different from AI/ML courses?</span>
					<Icon name="mdi:chevron-down" class="size-5 shrink-0 text-purple-500 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" />
				</summary>
				<p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
					This isn't about building AI. It's about being a better engineer with AI. No RAG pipelines,
					no fine-tuning. Practical workflows for shipping software faster.
				</p>
			</details>
			<details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-5 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-purple-300 dark:border-dark-border dark:bg-dark-surface dark:hover:border-purple-700">
				<summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
					<span>How long is the training?</span>
					<Icon name="mdi:chevron-down" class="size-5 shrink-0 text-purple-500 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" />
				</summary>
				<p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
					Tailored to your team. We scope the engagement based on your goals, team size, and depth needed.
				</p>
			</details>
			<details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-5 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-purple-300 dark:border-dark-border dark:bg-dark-surface dark:hover:border-purple-700">
				<summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
					<span>What's the ideal team size?</span>
					<Icon name="mdi:chevron-down" class="size-5 shrink-0 text-purple-500 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" />
				</summary>
				<p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
					5-15 engineers. Small enough for hands-on attention, large enough for rich discussion.
				</p>
			</details>
			<details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-5 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-purple-300 dark:border-dark-border dark:bg-dark-surface dark:hover:border-purple-700">
				<summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
					<span>Do we need AI experience?</span>
					<Icon name="mdi:chevron-down" class="size-5 shrink-0 text-purple-500 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" />
				</summary>
				<p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
					No. Strong software engineering fundamentals are the prerequisite. We start from first principles.
				</p>
			</details>
			<details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-5 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-purple-300 dark:border-dark-border dark:bg-dark-surface dark:hover:border-purple-700">
				<summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
					<span>What tools do you cover?</span>
					<Icon name="mdi:chevron-down" class="size-5 shrink-0 text-purple-500 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" />
				</summary>
				<p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
					Language-agnostic principles with hands-on time in tools like Claude Code, Cursor, GitHub Copilot, and others.
					Adapted to what your team uses or wants to adopt.
				</p>
			</details>
			<details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-5 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-purple-300 dark:border-dark-border dark:bg-dark-surface dark:hover:border-purple-700">
				<summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
					<span>Can we customize the curriculum?</span>
					<Icon name="mdi:chevron-down" class="size-5 shrink-0 text-purple-500 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" />
				</summary>
				<p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
					That's the point. The core modules are the baseline. We go deeper on what matters to your team.
				</p>
			</details>
			<details class="group rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-5 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-purple-300 dark:border-dark-border dark:bg-dark-surface dark:hover:border-purple-700">
				<summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">
					<span>What's the investment?</span>
					<Icon name="mdi:chevron-down" class="size-5 shrink-0 text-purple-500 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" />
				</summary>
				<p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
					Contact for pricing. Investment is based on team size and curriculum customization.
				</p>
			</details>
		</div>
	</Section>

	{/* Section 12: Final CTA */}
	<Section variant="dark" class="text-center">
		<h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold md:text-5xl">
			Ready to Make Your Team AI-Native?
		</h2>
		<p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-xl text-lg text-purple-100">
			Let's scope a training tailored to your team's goals and stack.
		</p>
		<div class="mt-10 flex flex-col items-center gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:justify-center">
			<CTA href={bookingUrl} label="Book a Call" />
			<CTA email={email} subject={subject} label="Or Email Me" variant="secondary" />
		</div>
	</Section>
</BaseLayout>
